The LLM failed to maintain functional parity during a complex library migration. 
While the developer carefully matched the original cryptographic padding (PKCS1v15), 
the LLM swapped it for PSS padding in its sign_sha256 implementation. 
Because PSS is non-deterministic, the resulting signatures would be incompatible with any legacy system expecting the original format.